2
00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:22.420
That's a new record, buddy.

3
00:00:22.420 --> 00:00:23.720
Well done.

4
00:00:23.720 --> 00:00:25.560
Let me check your blood pressure before you go, little fish.

5
00:00:25.560 --> 00:00:26.720
Hello, little mermaid.

6
00:00:26.720 --> 00:00:27.520
Hello, Minkong.

7
00:00:27.520 --> 00:00:28.620
Hello, Vadim.

8
00:00:28.720 --> 00:00:30.660
Take good care of our baby, will you?

9
00:00:30.660 --> 00:00:31.560
Mm-hmm.

10
00:00:31.560 --> 00:00:33.540
[sniffing]

11
00:00:33.540 --> 00:00:36.360
Why do I smell banana?

12
00:00:36.360 --> 00:00:37.740
It's my flavored lip balm.

13
00:00:37.740 --> 00:00:40.300
I picked it because I know how much you love bananas.

14
00:00:40.300 --> 00:00:41.780
[sniffing]

15
00:00:41.780 --> 00:00:42.580
Huh?

16
00:00:42.580 --> 00:00:47.380
I've got your nose.

17
00:00:47.380 --> 00:00:49.840
If you want it back, you'll have to catch me first.

18
00:00:49.840 --> 00:00:51.280
[laughing]

19
00:00:51.280 --> 00:00:52.860
You'd better run fast.

20
00:00:52.860 --> 00:00:55.760
[laughing]

21
00:00:55.760 --> 00:00:57.260
How about those two?

22
00:00:57.360 --> 00:00:58.920
Yeah, totally.

23
00:00:58.920 --> 00:01:01.760
Let's do this.

24
00:01:01.760 --> 00:01:06.300
In the daytime, I'm Marinette, just a normal girl

25
00:01:06.300 --> 00:01:08.040
with a normal life.

26
00:01:08.040 --> 00:01:11.240
But there's something about me that no one knows yet,

27
00:01:11.240 --> 00:01:12.740
because I've got a secret.

28
00:01:12.740 --> 00:01:15.640
(SINGING) Miraculous, simply the best.

29
00:01:15.640 --> 00:01:18.680
I'm to the best when things go wrong.

30
00:01:18.680 --> 00:01:21.640
Miraculous, the luck he has.

31
00:01:21.640 --> 00:01:24.620
The power of God always so strong.

32
00:01:24.720 --> 00:01:29.320
Miraculous, Miraculous, Miraculous.

33
00:01:29.320 --> 00:01:36.020
Don't tell me you're chatting with Nino again.

34
00:01:36.020 --> 00:01:38.100
You're seeing each other in less than an hour.

35
00:01:38.100 --> 00:01:40.000
I know, but he told me what he had for breakfast,

36
00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:41.660
and now he's saying that he's about to brush his teeth

37
00:01:41.660 --> 00:01:43.640
and go to the bathroom before he takes off.

38
00:01:43.640 --> 00:01:46.040
Whoa, you two really tell each other everything.

39
00:01:46.040 --> 00:01:47.140
Of course.

40
00:01:47.140 --> 00:01:48.880
Nino's my boyfriend and my best friend.

41
00:01:48.880 --> 00:01:51.740
We keep zero secrets from each other.

42
00:01:51.740 --> 00:01:53.640
I mean, almost zero secrets.

43
00:01:53.740 --> 00:01:57.740
You've got to keep a little mystery, right?

44
00:01:57.740 --> 00:01:59.620
Girls, do you tell your boyfriends

45
00:01:59.620 --> 00:02:00.860
or girlfriends everything, too?

46
00:02:00.860 --> 00:02:04.060
I tell Ivan everything, though he's a little more reserved.

47
00:02:04.060 --> 00:02:06.560
Like, I don't know a lot about his family, but it'll come.

48
00:02:06.560 --> 00:02:07.860
I know my teddy bear.

49
00:02:07.860 --> 00:02:09.720
What about you girls?

50
00:02:09.720 --> 00:02:11.960
I think we just really understand each other.

51
00:02:11.960 --> 00:02:13.060
Me too.

52
00:02:13.060 --> 00:02:14.300
You're lucky.

53
00:02:14.300 --> 00:02:15.560
My boyfriend's on the other side of the sea,

54
00:02:15.560 --> 00:02:17.460
which makes communication challenging.

55
00:02:17.460 --> 00:02:18.800
How do you do it, then?

56
00:02:18.800 --> 00:02:21.540
Oh.

57
00:02:21.640 --> 00:02:23.800
Video calls? What about you and Kim?

58
00:02:23.800 --> 00:02:24.800
How are things?

59
00:02:24.800 --> 00:02:27.780
Well, we laugh a lot.

60
00:02:27.780 --> 00:02:28.580
Awesome.

61
00:02:28.580 --> 00:02:29.720
It's so nice--

62
00:02:29.720 --> 00:02:32.120
Actually, I'm kind of worried about something.

63
00:02:32.120 --> 00:02:35.380
Truth is, we still haven't kissed.

64
00:02:35.380 --> 00:02:37.060
For real?

65
00:02:37.060 --> 00:02:38.680
And it's not just about kissing.

66
00:02:38.680 --> 00:02:41.320
He's never held my hand or told me that he loved me.

67
00:02:41.320 --> 00:02:44.960
Sometimes I wonder if we're even together.

68
00:02:44.960 --> 00:02:47.940
You know, some couples struggle with that kind of stuff.

69
00:02:47.940 --> 00:02:50.440
Things were like that for a while between me and Adrian.

70
00:02:50.540 --> 00:02:52.040
Does Kim know that you want to kiss?

71
00:02:52.040 --> 00:02:53.800
Maybe you need to ask him.

72
00:02:53.800 --> 00:02:55.100
That's not romantic at all.

73
00:02:55.100 --> 00:02:56.600
In fairy tales, the princess doesn't

74
00:02:56.600 --> 00:02:58.580
have to tell the prince that she wants him to kiss her.

75
00:02:58.580 --> 00:03:00.040
But fairy tales are just stories.

76
00:03:00.040 --> 00:03:01.540
Don't freak out too much about it.

77
00:03:01.540 --> 00:03:05.920
If he's the right dude, it'll happen when the time is right.

78
00:03:05.920 --> 00:03:06.980
You're right, Alia.

79
00:03:06.980 --> 00:03:08.580
Things happen when the time is right.

80
00:03:08.580 --> 00:03:11.160
And if it doesn't, then your BFFs can get involved.

81
00:03:11.160 --> 00:03:12.360
It's simple.

82
00:03:12.360 --> 00:03:13.960
We'll help Andine create the perfect moment

83
00:03:13.960 --> 00:03:15.260
for the first kiss.

84
00:03:15.260 --> 00:03:17.200
In my case, for example, Adrian was

85
00:03:17.200 --> 00:03:18.660
about to leave for London forever,

86
00:03:18.760 --> 00:03:20.660
so I grabbed my scooter and rushed to the airport,

87
00:03:20.660 --> 00:03:23.000
where I stopped him just before takeoff.

88
00:03:23.000 --> 00:03:26.340
Right then and there, we kissed for the first time.

89
00:03:26.340 --> 00:03:27.900
You can do the same thing.

90
00:03:27.900 --> 00:03:29.240
It won't work for me anyway.

91
00:03:29.240 --> 00:03:31.080
I'm not planning on leaving.

92
00:03:31.080 --> 00:03:32.580
And we don't have a plane.

93
00:03:32.580 --> 00:03:34.840
And I don't think Kim owns a scooter.

94
00:03:34.840 --> 00:03:37.340
Fine, it might not be the best of plans.

95
00:03:37.340 --> 00:03:40.480
Has one of you had a more simple first kiss?

96
00:03:40.480 --> 00:03:42.180
Ivan wrote a poem for me.

97
00:03:42.180 --> 00:03:43.760
It was super romantic.

98
00:03:43.760 --> 00:03:44.760
Perfect.

99
00:03:44.760 --> 00:03:46.220
That's a great idea. You could write him a poem.

100
00:03:46.220 --> 00:03:48.260
What do you think, Andine?

101
00:03:48.360 --> 00:03:50.220
It's a great idea.

102
00:03:50.220 --> 00:03:53.260
Thanks for your help, girls.

103
00:03:53.260 --> 00:03:55.300
Thanks for your help, girls.

104
00:03:55.300 --> 00:03:58.140
So who's going to break them up first?

105
00:03:58.140 --> 00:04:00.340
Rock, paper, scissors.

106
00:04:00.340 --> 00:04:02.340
Rock.

107
00:04:02.340 --> 00:04:04.900
I go first.

108
00:04:04.900 --> 00:04:06.380
I really loved your solo.

109
00:04:06.380 --> 00:04:07.840
You must have worked so hard on it.

110
00:04:07.840 --> 00:04:13.520
Whoa, those are so cool.

111
00:04:13.520 --> 00:04:15.080
You can have them if you want.

112
00:04:15.080 --> 00:04:15.980
For real?

113
00:04:15.980 --> 00:04:17.760
Awesome, thanks.

114
00:04:17.860 --> 00:04:21.060
But in exchange, you have to stop talking to girls.

115
00:04:21.060 --> 00:04:21.860
Really?

116
00:04:21.860 --> 00:04:22.560
Why?

117
00:04:22.560 --> 00:04:23.520
You don't need to know.

118
00:04:23.520 --> 00:04:24.760
Oh, OK.

119
00:04:24.760 --> 00:04:25.560
That's too funny.

120
00:04:25.560 --> 00:04:37.480
Your new shoes are very unique.

121
00:04:37.480 --> 00:04:38.280
Yeah.

122
00:04:38.280 --> 00:04:43.980
I want to read you something.

123
00:04:47.860 --> 00:04:50.800
[music playing]

124
00:04:50.800 --> 00:04:58.300
"Once upon a time, a sleeping siren

125
00:04:58.300 --> 00:05:02.000
dreamt of meeting her true love, a kind and gentle boy,

126
00:05:02.000 --> 00:05:05.500
not a tyrant, who would love her beyond and above.

127
00:05:05.500 --> 00:05:07.640
The siren feared she'd never meet him,

128
00:05:07.640 --> 00:05:09.940
for she thought she wasn't pretty enough.

129
00:05:09.940 --> 00:05:13.280
She was tall, too tall, with broad limbs and spots on her face

130
00:05:13.280 --> 00:05:15.680
that made it look rough."

131
00:05:15.680 --> 00:05:16.920
He's making a strange face.

132
00:05:17.020 --> 00:05:17.920
Don't you think?

133
00:05:17.920 --> 00:05:19.220
I guess it must be all the emotions.

134
00:05:19.220 --> 00:05:22.660
"Even in the worst of times, they would have fun.

135
00:05:22.660 --> 00:05:24.460
The siren had found her merman.

136
00:05:24.460 --> 00:05:25.420
What a bliss."

137
00:05:25.420 --> 00:05:26.760
This is going to work.

138
00:05:26.760 --> 00:05:28.000
I'm sure of it.

139
00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:30.960
"And when her prince finally graces her with a kiss,

140
00:05:30.960 --> 00:05:35.200
she will be the happiest princess in the ocean."

141
00:05:35.200 --> 00:05:36.400
[laughter]

142
00:05:36.400 --> 00:05:38.200
That's such a funny story.

143
00:05:38.200 --> 00:05:39.640
Wait, is he making fun of her?

144
00:05:39.640 --> 00:05:40.880
That's so rude.

145
00:05:40.880 --> 00:05:42.780
[laughter]

146
00:05:42.780 --> 00:05:43.840
It's not a story.

147
00:05:43.840 --> 00:05:44.840
It's a poem.

148
00:05:44.940 --> 00:05:47.780
And it's meant to be romantic, not funny.

149
00:05:47.780 --> 00:05:49.380
It's hilarious, though.

150
00:05:49.380 --> 00:05:51.220
There are even words that sound the same.

151
00:05:51.220 --> 00:05:54.060
And-- oh, no, dang.

152
00:05:54.060 --> 00:05:56.220
I just lost my flippers.

153
00:05:56.220 --> 00:05:56.920
Oh, man.

154
00:05:56.920 --> 00:06:03.700
I lost the challenge.

155
00:06:03.700 --> 00:06:05.740
But it's impossible not to talk to Ondine.

156
00:06:05.740 --> 00:06:06.700
She's really funny.

157
00:06:06.700 --> 00:06:14.840
If I can't do this, you two don't stand a chance.

158
00:06:14.940 --> 00:06:17.020
Heh, we'll see about that.

159
00:06:17.020 --> 00:06:19.320
Did you see him laughing?

160
00:06:19.320 --> 00:06:20.880
That wasn't very nice.

161
00:06:20.880 --> 00:06:24.220
Especially considering how beautiful your poem was.

162
00:06:24.220 --> 00:06:26.860
The truth is that he doesn't love me plain and simple.

163
00:06:26.860 --> 00:06:28.520
That's why he won't kiss me.

164
00:06:28.520 --> 00:06:29.660
That's not true.

165
00:06:29.660 --> 00:06:32.400
We just have to find the right scenario for you and Kim.

166
00:06:32.400 --> 00:06:33.460
We'll try something else.

167
00:06:33.460 --> 00:06:35.600
In Japan, we use biscuit sticks.

168
00:06:35.600 --> 00:06:36.940
It's the sweetheart's cookie.

169
00:06:36.940 --> 00:06:38.340
You're supposed to share it.

170
00:06:38.340 --> 00:06:40.100
You bite opposite ends of the same stick

171
00:06:40.100 --> 00:06:42.040
and nibble until your lips touch.

172
00:06:42.040 --> 00:06:44.880
OK, let's give it a try.

173
00:06:44.940 --> 00:06:48.880
[music playing]

174
00:06:48.880 --> 00:06:49.980
Hi, Loic.

175
00:06:49.980 --> 00:06:51.320
Your girlfriend.

176
00:06:51.320 --> 00:06:52.180
Ondine?

177
00:06:52.180 --> 00:06:53.180
Right.

178
00:06:53.180 --> 00:06:54.180
Don't touch her anymore.

179
00:06:54.180 --> 00:06:55.320
Don't talk to her anymore.

180
00:06:55.320 --> 00:06:56.780
Don't even look at her anymore.

181
00:06:56.780 --> 00:06:57.960
Huh? Why?

182
00:06:57.960 --> 00:06:59.320
Because I'm telling you, and when

183
00:06:59.320 --> 00:07:01.320
I tell you to do something, you just do it.

184
00:07:01.320 --> 00:07:04.060
OK, but then what do I do when I'm with her?

185
00:07:04.060 --> 00:07:05.300
You're no longer with her.

186
00:07:05.300 --> 00:07:06.300
Yes, I am.

187
00:07:06.300 --> 00:07:07.360
No, you're not.

188
00:07:07.360 --> 00:07:08.160
Yes, I am.

189
00:07:08.160 --> 00:07:09.300
No, you're not.

190
00:07:09.300 --> 00:07:10.200
Yes, I am.

191
00:07:10.200 --> 00:07:11.600
I'm telling you, you're not.

192
00:07:11.600 --> 00:07:13.300
And I'm telling you, I am.

193
00:07:13.400 --> 00:07:14.980
He's just too good.

194
00:07:14.980 --> 00:07:16.900
It's your plan that was bad.

195
00:07:16.900 --> 00:07:20.820
[music playing]

196
00:07:20.820 --> 00:07:23.320
[humming]

197
00:07:23.320 --> 00:07:26.380
[hissing]

198
00:07:26.380 --> 00:07:27.380
Hm?

199
00:07:27.380 --> 00:07:38.300
[music playing]

200
00:07:38.300 --> 00:07:39.960
Delicious.

201
00:07:39.960 --> 00:07:41.540
Another one?

202
00:07:41.540 --> 00:07:42.360
And another?

203
00:07:43.460 --> 00:07:44.900
Ondine?

204
00:07:44.900 --> 00:07:46.100
What are you doing here?

205
00:07:46.100 --> 00:07:53.980
Did you find some, too?

206
00:07:53.980 --> 00:07:55.280
They're so yummy.

207
00:07:55.280 --> 00:08:00.880
Hm, hm, hm, hm, hm, hm, hm.

208
00:08:00.880 --> 00:08:01.780
Oh.

209
00:08:01.780 --> 00:08:03.560
Oh.

210
00:08:03.560 --> 00:08:06.460
Ah.

211
00:08:06.460 --> 00:08:07.460
Oh.

212
00:08:07.460 --> 00:08:09.020
What are you doing?

213
00:08:09.020 --> 00:08:11.020
Well, you didn't look like you were going to finish it,

214
00:08:11.020 --> 00:08:12.260
so I ate it.

215
00:08:12.360 --> 00:08:14.900
You never get anything right.

216
00:08:14.900 --> 00:08:16.800
Why won't you kiss me?

217
00:08:16.800 --> 00:08:19.440
But what for?

218
00:08:19.440 --> 00:08:22.580
I love you, Kim, but sometimes I can't help but wonder why.

219
00:08:22.580 --> 00:08:33.380
[crying]

220
00:08:33.380 --> 00:08:35.480
You're so right, you know.

221
00:08:35.480 --> 00:08:36.820
What do you mean I'm right?

222
00:08:36.820 --> 00:08:38.220
Not to kiss her.

223
00:08:38.220 --> 00:08:39.560
It's disgusting.

224
00:08:39.560 --> 00:08:41.760
Did you know that kissing increases your heart rate

225
00:08:41.860 --> 00:08:44.260
and that the exchange of saliva can transfer hundreds

226
00:08:44.260 --> 00:08:46.160
of different bacteria strains?

227
00:08:46.160 --> 00:08:47.300
Really?

228
00:08:47.300 --> 00:08:50.000
But the real problem is when the girl is a swimmer,

229
00:08:50.000 --> 00:08:52.300
then it becomes seriously dangerous.

230
00:08:52.300 --> 00:08:54.100
You can turn into a toad.

231
00:08:54.100 --> 00:08:55.040
Huh?

232
00:08:55.040 --> 00:08:56.800
No way, that only happens in fairy tales.

233
00:08:56.800 --> 00:08:59.540
In every fairy tale, there's an element of truth, you know.

234
00:08:59.540 --> 00:09:01.040
Take her, for example.

235
00:09:01.040 --> 00:09:02.240
Ondine?

236
00:09:02.240 --> 00:09:03.740
All of her swimming causes the presence

237
00:09:03.740 --> 00:09:05.820
of specific bacteria in her mouth.

238
00:09:05.820 --> 00:09:08.280
And if you kiss her and catch her bacteria,

239
00:09:08.280 --> 00:09:11.160
warts will grow on your back, like with toads.

240
00:09:11.260 --> 00:09:13.560
And on top of that, if the girl is taller than you,

241
00:09:13.560 --> 00:09:15.360
then you must never kiss her.

242
00:09:15.360 --> 00:09:16.920
Both your lives would be at stake.

243
00:09:16.920 --> 00:09:19.160
It would cause an anaphylectic shock.

244
00:09:19.160 --> 00:09:20.000
What?

245
00:09:20.000 --> 00:09:23.600
Swelling, choking, boom, on the floor, both of you.

246
00:09:23.600 --> 00:09:25.400
That sounds horrible.

247
00:09:25.400 --> 00:09:28.000
Absolute horror, indeed.

248
00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:29.840
I give up, he's not into it.

249
00:09:29.840 --> 00:09:31.340
I'm not going to force him.

250
00:09:31.340 --> 00:09:34.140
You're right, it's probably best to throw in the towel.

251
00:09:34.140 --> 00:09:37.640
Maybe he's not worthy of your feelings.

252
00:09:37.640 --> 00:09:39.320
No towels will be thrown in.

253
00:09:39.420 --> 00:09:41.320
We just haven't figured out the right approach

254
00:09:41.320 --> 00:09:42.860
to make him understand yet.

255
00:09:42.860 --> 00:09:46.060
But I'm sure we can rise to the challenge.

256
00:09:46.060 --> 00:09:47.660
Of course, a challenge.

257
00:09:47.660 --> 00:09:48.900
Great idea, Marinette.

258
00:09:48.900 --> 00:09:51.400
Thank you.

259
00:09:51.400 --> 00:09:59.600
Uh, what was my idea exactly?

260
00:09:59.600 --> 00:10:00.900
Come on, arm wrestling.

261
00:10:00.900 --> 00:10:02.240
Loser has to do it there.

262
00:10:02.240 --> 00:10:03.440
What, now?

263
00:10:03.440 --> 00:10:05.080
So you're not up for it?

264
00:10:05.080 --> 00:10:06.640
Of course I'm up for it.

265
00:10:09.480 --> 00:10:10.380
Now for the dare.

266
00:10:10.380 --> 00:10:11.760
You must give me a kiss.

267
00:10:11.760 --> 00:10:20.920
Couldn't we just do best of three?

268
00:10:20.920 --> 00:10:22.760
Huh?

269
00:10:22.760 --> 00:10:23.960
Don't you love me?

270
00:10:23.960 --> 00:10:25.160
Is this why you won't kiss me?

271
00:10:25.160 --> 00:10:26.400
You can tell me, you know.

272
00:10:26.400 --> 00:10:29.300
No, it's just because that it's disgusting.

273
00:10:29.300 --> 00:10:31.540
Because of all the swimming bacteria.

274
00:10:31.540 --> 00:10:34.380
I'm sorry, but I don't want to turn into a toad.

275
00:10:34.380 --> 00:10:36.740
What are you talking about?

276
00:10:36.740 --> 00:10:38.780
Your bacteria causes warts.

277
00:10:38.880 --> 00:10:41.340
If that's a joke because you don't feel ready,

278
00:10:41.340 --> 00:10:42.980
